[img[https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Notre_Dame_de_Chartres.jpg/500px-Notre_Dame_de_Chartres.jpg]]

A famous [[Catholic]] cathedral in Chartres, [[France]], and the seat of the Bishop of Chartres. Built mainly between [[1194|1100s]] and [[1250|1200s]] above earlier [[Romanesque]] basements, it contains the most famous and influential examples of [[High Gothic]] and [[Classic Gothic]] architecture. It's north spire is the newest section, built in the ornate [[Flamboyant]] style during 1507-1513.
